Day 22 — Power Pivot

Today I moved beyond Power Query into Power Pivot to practice data modeling and analytical calculations using a sample dataset.

🔹 Dataset
	•	Random sales dataset used for practice
	•	Included customer, product, sales price, cost, and employee data

🔹 What I Built
	•	Created a calculated column for TOTAL PROFIT
	•	Loaded data into the Power Pivot data model
	•	Built a PivotTable to analyze profit by employee
	•	Practiced foundational DAX thinking

🔹 Key Learnings
	•	Power Pivot enables true data modeling inside Excel
	•	Calculated columns help derive business metrics
	•	PivotTables connected to the data model are more powerful
	•	Understanding DAX is essential for advanced analytics